<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="171" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="171">Comments</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="171">
<bibRefCitation author="Broadley, DG" journalOrPublisher="African Journal of Herpetology" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" pagination="95 - 112" publicationUrl="10.1080/21564574.2006.9635543" refId="B23" refString="Broadley, DG, Whiting, SA, Bauer, AM, 2006. A revision of East Africa species of Melanoseps Boulenger (Sauria: Scincidae: Feylininae). African Journal of Herpetology 55: 95 - 112, DOI: 10.1080/21564574.2006.9635543" title="A revision of East Africa species of Melanoseps Boulenger (Sauria: Scincidae: Feylininae)." url="10.1080/21564574.2006.9635543" volume="55" year="2006">Broadley et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
assigned the northern Mozambique specimens to 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Melanoseps" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanoseps loveridgei" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="171" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="loveridgei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">Melanoseps loveridgei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while specimens from southern Malawi are referred to as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Guenther" baseAuthorityYear="1873" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Melanoseps" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanoseps ater" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="171" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">Melanoseps ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We used the key from 
<bibRefCitation author="Broadley, DG" journalOrPublisher="African Journal of Herpetology" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" pagination="95 - 112" publicationUrl="10.1080/21564574.2006.9635543" refId="B23" refString="Broadley, DG, Whiting, SA, Bauer, AM, 2006. A revision of East Africa species of Melanoseps Boulenger (Sauria: Scincidae: Feylininae). African Journal of Herpetology 55: 95 - 112, DOI: 10.1080/21564574.2006.9635543" title="A revision of East Africa species of Melanoseps Boulenger (Sauria: Scincidae: Feylininae)." url="10.1080/21564574.2006.9635543" volume="55" year="2006">Broadley et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
to identify the specimens based on number mid-body scale rows (24). 
<bibRefCitation author="Timberlake, JR" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, London" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" publicationUrl="http://www.kew.org/sites/default/files/kppcont_067897.pdf" refId="B69" refString="Timberlake, JR, Bayliss, J, Dowsett-Lemaire, F, Conghan, C, Branch, WR, Collins, S, Curran, M, Dowsett, RJ, Fishpool, L, Francisco, J, Harris, T, Kopp, M, de Sousa, C, 2012. Mt. Mabu, Mozambique: Biodiversity and Conservation. In: Report produced under the Darwin Initiative Award 15/036. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, London, http://www.kew.org/sites/default/files/kppcont_067897.pdf" title="Mt. Mabu, Mozambique: Biodiversity and Conservation." url="http://www.kew.org/sites/default/files/kppcont_067897.pdf" volumeTitle="Report produced under the Darwin Initiative Award 15 / 036." year="2012">Timberlake et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
were the first to report this species from Mt. Mabu and this was only the second record for this genus in Mozambique. 
<bibRefCitation author="Farooq, HOM" journalOrPublisher="Herpetology Notes" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" pagination="59 - 62" refId="B38" refString="Farooq, HOM, Conradie, W, 2015. A second record of Scolecomorphus kirkii Boulenger, 1883 (Gymnophiona: Scolecomorphidae) for Mozambique. Herpetology Notes 8: 59 - 62" title="A second record of Scolecomorphus kirkii Boulenger, 1883 (Gymnophiona: Scolecomorphidae) for Mozambique." volume="8" year="2015">Farooq and Conradie (2015)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Melanoseps" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanoseps loveridgei" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="171" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="loveridgei">Melanoseps cf. loveridgei</taxonomicName>
from Mt. Namuli. This identification was tentative, as material got lost in a motor vehicle accident and could not be examined. Based on the close proximity to Mt. Mabu the Mt. Namuli record should be regarded as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Guenther" baseAuthorityYear="1873" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Melanoseps" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanoseps ater" order="Squamata" pageId="8" pageNumber="171" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">Melanoseps cf. ater</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
